<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
  i18n:domain="launchpad"
>

<head>
  <style metal:fill-slot="head_epilogue" type="text/css">
    #chooseLinks {
      width:1000px;
      margin:0;
      padding:0;
    }
    #chooseLinks a 
    {
      width:25%;
      display:block;
      margin:1em;
      float:left;
      padding:1em;
      border: .1em solid #DBA73A;
      text-align:center;
      font-size:85%;
      text-decoration: none;
      height: 4em;
    }
    #chooseLinks div {
      width:100%;
      margin: auto 0;
    }
    #chooseLinks a:hover {
      background-color: #FFE8BF;
    }
    #chooseLinks a span {
      font-weight: bold;
      text-decoration:underline;
    }
    #chooseLinks a strong {
      font-size:100%;
    }
    #downloadOptions li {
      margin: .4em 0;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <div metal:fill-slot="body">
  <tal:block define="flavour_name view/flavour/title;
                     series_name view/series/title">
  
    <h1>Requesting CDs from ShipIt</h1>

    <p>Ubuntu is available free of charge and we can send you CDs of the
    latest version (<span tal:replace="series_name" />) with no extra
    cost, but the delivery may take up to ten weeks, so you should consider
    downloading the CD images if you have a fast Internet connection.
    </p>
    
    <div id="chooseLinks">
      <tal:no-prerelease condition="not: view/prerelease_mode">
        <div>
          <a tal:attributes="href view/download_or_buy_link">
            I want to <span>download</span>
            <span tal:replace="flavour_name">Ubuntu</span>
            <span tal:replace="series_name" /></a>
        </div>
        <div>
          <a href="login">
            I want to <span>request CDs</span> of
            <span tal:replace="flavour_name">Ubuntu</span>
            <span tal:replace="series_name" /></a>
        </div>
        <div tal:condition="view/flavour/enumvalue:UBUNTU">
          <a href="login-server">
            I want to <span>request CDs of Ubuntu Server Edition</span>
            <span tal:replace="series_name" /></a>
        </div>
      </tal:no-prerelease>
      <tal:prerelease condition="view/prerelease_mode">
        <div>
          <a tal:attributes="href view/beta_download_link">
            I want to <span>download and test</span> the beta version of
            <span tal:replace="series_name" /></a>
        </div>
        <div>
          <a href="login">
            I want to <span>pre-order CDs</span> of
            <span tal:replace="flavour_name">Ubuntu</span>
            <span tal:replace="series_name" /></a>
        </div>
        <div tal:condition="view/flavour/enumvalue:UBUNTU">
          <a href="login-server">
            I want to <span>pre-order CDs of Ubuntu Server Edition</span>
            <span tal:replace="series_name" /></a>
        </div>
      </tal:prerelease>
    </div>
  
    <div class="visualClear body">&nbsp;</div>

      <h1>Other ways of getting <span tal:replace="flavour_name">Ubuntu</span></h1>

      <ul id="downloadOptions">
        <li><a href="http://www.ubuntu.com/getubuntu/purchase#distributor"
          >Purchase a CD from one of our world-wide distributors</a></li>
        <li><a href="http://www.ubuntu.com/getubuntu/purchase#bulk"
          >Buy CDs in large quantities</a></li>
        <li tal:condition="not: view/flavour/enumvalue:EDUBUNTU">
          <a href="http://www.ubuntu.com/getubuntu/purchase#buy"
            >Purchase DVDs from online retailers</a></li>
      </ul>

    <p><a href="login">Check the status of an existing request</a></p>

  </tal:block>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
